                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>70 14 1 0</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" valign="bottom" align="center">
                                <para>Air Powered Park Brake is stuck.</para>
                                <para>Occurs when the park brake switch does not match the spring apply air release
                                    (SAAR) chamber travel sensor. This indicates the park brake cannot be applied or
                                    cannot be released.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>70 14 1 1</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" valign="bottom" align="center">
                                <para>The auto apply portion with the Air Powered Park Brake is not operating.</para>
                                <para>Occurs when the park brake switch is not set within 5 seconds of the receipt of
                                    the Park as the requested gear. This failure would indicate a failure in the auto
                                    apply or in the air lines between the auto apply relay and the Park Brake switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
